2021-01-16T23:26:05Z	📣 **NEW:** The "Twt Blog" feature here on [twtxt.net](https://twtxt.net) (_and others pods, if updated_, cc @xuu @etux) now support rendering Twtxt URI(s) and Hashtag(s). You can mention a local pod user with `@johndoe` or a remote pod user with `@johndoe@domain.tld`. You can even mention traditional Twtxt users with the regular @`<nick url>` syntax and #`hashtag` are also fully supported (_which link to your local pod_). Happy Twt Blogging! 🤗
